cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as depth estimation and image decomposition, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also proposes a novel convolutional neural network architecture, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning, i.e., cs.LG. The use of conditional random fields (CRFs) in the joint estimation problem suggests the involvement of probabilistic graphical models, which is a sub-field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of gradient domain processing, which is a technique commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
